Herpaderp, simplify the remainder test for now:

* Needed to return to mock_remote because just testing Connection
  doesn't prove that we got two distinct connections handed to
  the tasks, only that Connection() ran twice (it would result in
  both tasks having the same, second/last, Connection instance).
* Then had to scale back to a single host in host list because
  mock_remote can't handle >1 run() call per session, sigh. Things
  like exit_status_ready's side effect run out too fast.
* Best to have the test be simple anyways and expand later on.
* Did not commit this, but it only works if Connection inherits
  from invoke.Context. Want to make sure that is done correctly
  before committing it.

Skel tests for more corner cases re: exception handling

Realized these don't actually make as much sense.

Was basing off how invoke ThreadException wraps N exceptions...but that is because
it was written to handle N sibling IO threads that all want their exceptions
treated equally. In the tunnel use case, tunnels do not know if they are being
run at the same time as others; only the first context manager to exit gets to
raise anything.

Similarly, manager-vs-inner-tunnel exceptions don't feel like they need to be
bundled up either, at least for now.

Use ExceptionHandlingThread & friends for tunnel thread classes.

commit_message:
Patch pathlib.Path for safety

Some get() tests don't need to patch on their own,
so then this tends to bleed mkdirs
Sphinx anchor was causing two separate params lists, weird
flake8 and oops pathlib2 does not show up as pathlib, my bad, sorry

Add default issue template

In order to try to improve the quality of issues and prevent issues being raised against the wrong repository
Format tweaks to bugreport template, and try slapping in a link to contribution-guide
More issue template tweaks

Removing global-scope configuration for replacing environment variables, replacing with specific override to clear environment only for remote.

Issue: fabric/fabric#2142
See also: 4358f344e5d6b59dc99d954ad8287b4021d0ed81
Feedback: the kwarg override should be "gentle" and use kwargs.setdefault in case a user is explicitly giving it for some reason

Feedback: there ought to be another test proving that this kwarg override is happening (currently the test change only proves that the config override is not happening) and also proving the setdefault is working (caller can override)
